race.comment: BACCARAT ROUGE (3) raced just off the lead before lifting to score by 1L lengths over 1900m at Kilcoy last start. Uses the inside barrier and keeps the handy 2kg claim. A strong winning hope. DECARBONISE (8) came back in trip and was expected to win at Kilcoy but was slow away and wide after. His effort over 1800m at the Gold Coast prior reads well enough. BOLD TYRANT (9) was better here last time when closing off nicely into fourth. Will appreciate the rise to 2000m and is hitting his straps now. Big chance. BETA BETTER (4) was denied by the barest of margins last time at Ballina. Fitter and is another that will appreciate the added trip.
